## System classification
 
| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| EU AI Act risk tier | HIGH-RISK |
| Annex III reference | Category 5(b) — access to essential private services |
| Deployment context | Real-time transaction fraud scoring across retail current account and card products |
| Geographies | UK, Ireland, EU passporting jurisdictions |
| Classification date | 2026-01-15 |
| Classification owner | Head of Model Risk |
 
**Classification rationale:** FraudGuard ML produces a real-time fraud probability score for each transaction. Scores above a defined threshold result in automated transaction blocking. This constitutes a materially automated decision affecting customer access to financial services. The decision is consequential — a false positive freezes a legitimate customer's account; a false negative enables fraud that causes customer harm. Classification as high-risk under Annex III Category 5(b) is confirmed.
 
